Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and 3/4 cup water (1¼ cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Toss with lime zest.

Meanwhile, pat @pork cutlets{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with salt and pepper; rub all over with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. (For 4 servings, cook in batches if necessary.)

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add 1/4 cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings), @miso sauce concentrate{1}, @honey{1/2%ounce}, and a big squeeze of lime juice. Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @butter{2%tbsp}. Taste and season with salt, pepper, and more lime juice if desired.

Return pork to pan and turn to coat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, pork, and carrots between plates. Top pork with any remaining sauce. Sprinkle everything with scallion greens and as many @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> The pork is drizzled with a life-affirming, sweet and savory miso-lime sauce. Talk about a dream come true!